-- UBS Hires Daisaku Ueno From Gaitame as a Currency Strategist in Tokyo
-- B y   S h i g e k i   N o z a w a   a n d   M a r i k o   I s h i k a w a
-- 2011-12-21T05:38:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/ubs-hires-daisaku-ueno-from-gaitame-as-a-currency-strategist-in-tokyo.html
UBS AG,  Switzerland ’s biggest bank,
said it hired  Daisaku Ueno  as a currency strategist based in
 Tokyo .  Ueno, who joins from Gaitame.com Research Institute Ltd.,
will start on Jan. 4 and report to Mansoor Mohi-uddin, UBS’s
Singapore-based head of foreign-exchange strategy, spokeswoman
Eiko Noda said in an e-mailed statement today. Ueno previously
worked for Nomura Securities.  To contact the reporters on this story:
